# Mod Metadata Guidelines

## About.xml Structure
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ModMetaData>
    <name>RimAsync</name>
    <author>Ilya Volkov</author>
    <packageId>rimasync.mod</packageId>
    <supportedVersions>
        <li>1.5</li>
    </supportedVersions>
    <description>
        RimAsync provides asynchronous performance improvements for RimWorld while maintaining full compatibility with multiplayer.
        
        The first performance mod that works in multiplayer environments!
        
        Features:
        - Asynchronous pathfinding and job processing
        - Full RimWorld Multiplayer compatibility
        - Significant TPS improvements on large colonies
        - Intelligent caching systems
        - Automatic performance scaling
        
        LOAD ORDER: Place after RimWorld Multiplayer if using multiplayer.
        
        Compatible with most mods. Report issues on GitHub.
    </description>
    <modDependencies>
        <li>
            <packageId>brrainz.harmony</packageId>
            <displayName>Harmony</displayName>
            <steamWorkshopUrl>steam://url/CommunityFilePage/2009463077</steamWorkshopUrl>
            <downloadUrl>https://github.com/pardeike/HarmonyRimWorld/releases/latest</downloadUrl>
        </li>
    </modDependencies>
    <loadAfter>
        <li>rwmt.Multiplayer</li>
    </loadAfter>
    <incompatibleWith>
        <li>majorhoff.rimthreaded</li>
    </incompatibleWith>
</ModMetaData>
```

